memories, to me, are the most
powerful life force we have

00:49:57.980 --> 00:49:59.680
available to us.

00:49:59.680 --> 00:50:03.740
When you think about it,
memories have kept prisoners

00:50:03.740 --> 00:50:05.270
of war alive.

00:50:05.270 --> 00:50:07.210
Memories have brought families
together when

00:50:07.210 --> 00:50:08.820
they were miles apart.

00:50:08.820 --> 00:50:10.260
They've helped heal the sick.

00:50:10.260 --> 00:50:12.430
They've sped up recovery
times.

00:50:12.430 --> 00:50:14.010
Memories are a powerful tool.

00:50:14.010 --> 00:50:18.220
And frankly, in the
end, members are

00:50:18.220 --> 00:50:20.510
all you'll ever have.

00:50:20.510 --> 00:50:21.400
It's not your money.

00:50:21.400 --> 00:50:24.920
It's not your big houses, not
your nice, designer clothes.

00:50:28.020 --> 00:50:29.650
Because when you die, everything
goes back in the

00:50:29.650 --> 00:50:31.840
box, including you.

00:50:31.840 --> 00:50:32.620
So memories--

00:50:32.620 --> 00:50:36.740
please make, please make
memories a top priority.

00:50:36.740 --> 00:50:39.430
If you have great memories, you
will always have a place

00:50:39.430 --> 00:50:41.340
to go when times are tough.

00:50:41.340 --> 00:50:43.150
And the last is tradition.

00:50:43.150 --> 00:50:46.600
Give your family something that
lives on long after you.

00:50:46.600 --> 00:50:49.040
Maybe, your parents have
done that for you.

00:50:49.040 --> 00:50:51.080
That's three greatest gifts
you can give to

00:50:51.080 --> 00:50:54.540
your family, I believe.

